The paper focuses on evaluating human-robot social interactions, which is a topic that falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the design and implementation of a software platform for the interaction paradigm, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for analyzing the social interactions, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of computer vision for tracking the interactions, which falls under the category of Computer Vision (cs.CV).
